  "prompt": "How much refund will I get on my PRS counter ticket if my seat is waitlisted even after the departure of the train? Can I board the train using it",
  "response": "If your seat on a PRS (Passenger Reservation System) counter ticket remains waitlisted even after the departure of the train, you are entitled to a full refund of the ticket amount. However, to claim this refund, you need to surrender your ticket within the specified time limits set by Indian Railways. Typically, you must submit your ticket for a refund within three days of the train's departure if it was purchased from a PRS counter.\n\nRegarding boarding the train with a waitlisted ticket, you are not allowed to board the train if your ticket status remains waitlisted at the time of the train's departure. Indian Railways does not permit passengers with waitlisted tickets to travel, and you may be considered a ticketless traveler if you attempt to board the train under these circumstances, which could result in fines or other penalties.\n\nTo summarize:\n- You can get a full refund if your ticket remains waitlisted after the train's departure, provided you surrender it within the stipulated time.\n- You cannot board the train with a waitlisted ticket.",
